{
  "texts": [
    "Initially, the study examines how AI, specifically Generative AI (GenAI) models like ChatGPT and Google Gemini, respond to key environmental science education questions using a diverse set of prompts.",
    "Subsequently, it evaluates the AI responses for accuracy, relevance, depth, creativity, and semantic clarity.",
    "The objective is to critically assess and compare the capabilities of these leading AI technologies within the specialized field of environmental science.",
    "Lastly, the paper discusses the implications of employing GenAI models in both teaching and learning processes, highlighting the potential benefits and challenges of integrating these technologies into educational frameworks.",
    "The methodology for this research is divided into several key stages: question creation, data collection through AI responses, expert evaluation using four metrics, knowledge graph construction, and visualization."
  ]
}